{"title_page": "Zellyka Arce", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Zellyka Arce\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Zellyka Guadalupe Arce Balleza\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|7|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Lagos de Moreno]], [[Jalisco]], Mexico\n| height = 1.63 m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Atlas]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Guadalajara]]\n| caps1 = 14\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[Club Atlas]] \n| caps2 = 49\n| goals2 = 5\n}}\n\n'''Zellyka Guadalupe Arce Balleza'''{{efn Spanish name|Arce|Balleza}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/jugador/125590/zellyka-guadalupe-arce-balleza |title=Zellyka Arce |work=[[Liga MX Femenil]] |language=Spanish |date= |accessdate=September 30, 2017 |publisher=Liga MX Femenil}}</ref> (born 28 July 1997), known as '''Zellyka Arce''', is a Mexican professional [[association football|football]] [[midfielder]] who currently plays for [[Club Atlas (Women)|Atlas]] (femenil)<ref name=\"asdiario-120817\">{{Cite news |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2017/12/08/futbol/1512689816_155200.html |title=Chivas femenil deja atr\u00e1s el t\u00edtulo y se enfoca en lo que viene |last=AS |first=Diario |date=2017-12-07 |work=AS M\u00e9xico |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-mx}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eloccidental.com.mx/deportes/la-mentalidad-es-ir-por-el-bicampeonato-zellyka-arce-de-chivas-femenil-1290558.html |title=La mentalidad es ir por el bicampeonato: Zellyka Arce de Chivas Femenil |work=El Occidental |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-MX}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ntrguadalajara.com/post.php?id_nota=85189 |title=Vengan esas \u00c1guilas  {{!}} NTR Guadalajara|website=www.ntrguadalajara.com|language=es|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/2017/11/01/en-el-clasico-nacional-femenil-hay-amigas-y-rivales |title=En el cl\u00e1sico nacional femenil hay amigas y rivales |work=MedioTiempo |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-MX}}</ref> of the Mexican [[Liga MX Femenil]], the first professional women's soccer league in Mexico.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/liga-bancomer/22/blog/post/3485437/brilliant-liga-mx-femenil-final-the-cherry-on-top-of-a-groundbreaking-debut-season |title=Femenil final shows women's football is thriving in Mexico |work=ESPN.com |access-date=2018-05-11}}</ref> \nIn 2017, she contributed to Chivas win the first professional women's football championship in the country in front of a record-setting 32,466 spectators.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.publimetro.com.mx/mx/publisport/2017/12/07/chivas-femenil-ya-suena-bicampeonato-la-liga-mx.html |title=Chivas femenil ya sue\u00f1a con el bicampeonato de la Liga MX |website=Publimetro M\u00e9xico |language=es-ES |access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://deportes.televisa.com/futbol/chivas-vs-pachuca-en-vivo/ |title=Cr\u00f3nica Chivas vs Pachuca, Final Liga MX Femenil |last=Redacci\u00f3n |date=2017-11-24 |work=Deportes Production |access-date=2018-05-11 |language=es-MX}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\n=== Guadalajara, 2017\u2013 ===\nArce played for [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Guadalajara]] during the [[2017\u201318 Liga MX Femenil season|inaugural season]] of [[Liga MX Femenil]].<ref name=\"asdiario-120817\"/> Honours\n\n===Club===\n;Guadalajara\n*[[Liga MX Femenil]]: [[2017\u201318 Liga MX Femenil season#Torneo Apertura|Apertura 2017]]\n\n'''[[Club Atlas (Women)|Club Atlas]]'''\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Liga MX Femenil player|125590|Zellyka Guadalupe Arce Balleza}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180701083449/http://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/campus/detalle/493 Zellyka Arce] at [[C.D. Guadalajara Femenil]] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{C.D. Guadalajara (Women) squad}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Arce, Zellyka}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Jalisco]]\n[[Category:Mexican women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Liga MX Femenil players]]\n[[Category:Women's association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{Mexico-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Zellyka Arce\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Zellyka Guadalupe Arce Balleza\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|7|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Lagos de Moreno]], [[Jalisco]], Mexico\n| height = 1.63 m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Atlas]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Guadalajara]]\n| caps1 = 14\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[Club Atlas]] \n| caps2 = 49\n| goals2 = 5\n}}\n\n'''Zellyka Guadalupe Arce Balleza'''{{efn Spanish name|Arce|Balleza}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/jugador/125590/zellyka-guadalupe-arce-balleza |title=Zellyka Arce |work=[[Liga MX Femenil]] |language=Spanish |date= |accessdate=September 30, 2017 |publisher=Liga MX Femenil}}</ref> (born 28 July 1997), known as '''Zellyka Arce''', is a Mexican professional [[association football|football]] [[midfielder]] who currently plays for [[Club Atlas (Women)|Atlas]] (femenil)<ref name=\"asdiario-120817\">{{Cite news |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2017/12/08/futbol/1512689816_155200.html |title=Chivas femenil deja atr\u00e1s el t\u00edtulo y se enfoca en lo que viene |last=AS |first=Diario |date=2017-12-07 |work=AS M\u00e9xico |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-mx}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eloccidental.com.mx/deportes/la-mentalidad-es-ir-por-el-bicampeonato-zellyka-arce-de-chivas-femenil-1290558.html |title=La mentalidad es ir por el bicampeonato: Zellyka Arce de Chivas Femenil |work=El Occidental |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-MX}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ntrguadalajara.com/post.php?id_nota=85189 |title=Vengan esas \u00c1guilas  {{!}} NTR Guadalajara|website=www.ntrguadalajara.com|language=es|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/2017/11/01/en-el-clasico-nacional-femenil-hay-amigas-y-rivales |title=En el cl\u00e1sico nacional femenil hay amigas y rivales |work=MedioTiempo |access-date=2018-05-12 |language=es-MX}}</ref>of the Mexican [[Liga MX Femenil]], the first professional women's soccer league in Mexico.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/liga-bancomer/22/blog/post/3485437/brilliant-liga-mx-femenil-final-the-cherry-on-top-of-a-groundbreaking-debut-season |title=Femenil final shows women's football is thriving in Mexico |work=ESPN.com |access-date=2018-05-11}}</ref> \nIn 2017, she contributed to Chivas win the first professional women's football championship in the country in front of a record-setting 32,466 spectators.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.publimetro.com.mx/mx/publisport/2017/12/07/chivas-femenil-ya-suena-bicampeonato-la-liga-mx.html |title=Chivas femenil ya sue\u00f1a con el bicampeonato de la Liga MX |website=Publimetro M\u00e9xico |language=es-ES |access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://deportes.televisa.com/futbol/chivas-vs-pachuca-en-vivo/ |title=Cr\u00f3nica Chivas vs Pachuca, Final Liga MX Femenil |last=Redacci\u00f3n |date=2017-11-24 |work=Deportes Production |access-date=2018-05-11 |language=es-MX}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\n=== Guadalajara, 2017\u2013 ===\nArce played for [[C.D. Guadalajara (Women)|Guadalajara]] during the [[2017\u201318 Liga MX Femenil season|inaugural season]] of [[Liga MX Femenil]].<ref name=\"asdiario-120817\"/>Honours\n===Club===\n;Guadalajara\n*[[Liga MX Femenil]]: [[2017\u201318 Liga MX Femenil season#Torneo Apertura|Apertura 2017]]\n\n'''[[Club Atlas (Women)|Club Atlas]]'''\n \n\n\n\n<br />\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n